    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) <strong>half </strong>your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>remaining garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/red-wine-fable-mushroom-ragu-tortiglioni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced carrot</strong> and <strong>sliced shallot </strong>to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until the veg is slightly softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/red-wine-fable-mushroom-ragu-tortiglioni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the veg is softening, add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>pasta </strong>for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/red-wine-fable-mushroom-ragu-tortiglioni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, reboil half a kettle</p><p>Shred your <strong>Fable pulled mushrooms</strong> apart using two forks</p><p>Once the veg is slightly softened, add the <strong>shredded mushrooms</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min further or until the mushrooms are browned</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/red-wine-fable-mushroom-ragu-tortiglioni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong> to the pan with your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>red wine paste</strong> and <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>with your <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for 5-7 min further or until the sauce has thickened and the carrot is completely softened</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/red-wine-fable-mushroom-ragu-tortiglioni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook, stirring frequently, for 3-4 min further or until golden</p><p>Once golden, transfer to a small bowl and set aside \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic pangrattato</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/red-wine-fable-mushroom-ragu-tortiglioni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, add the <strong>drained pasta </strong>to the sauce<strong> </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for 1-2 min or until the pasta is evenly coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your <strong>red wine Fable mushroom rag\u00f9 pasta</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of the starchy pasta water<strong> </strong>if it's looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/red-wine-fable-mushroom-ragu-tortiglioni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>red wine Fable mushroom rag\u00f9 tortiglioni </strong>in a bowl and sprinkle the<strong> garlic pangrattato </strong>over the top</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
